value.value: Helicases are a class of enzymes that utilize the energy of ATP hydrolysis to promote unwinding of 1.) label.value: Autologous KRAS Mutant-specific TCRs Gene Engineered PBLs

value.value: A preparation of autologous peripheral blood lymphocytes (PBLs) that have been genetically modified to express T-cell receptors (TCRs) specific for K-RAS (KRAS) mutations, with potential immunomodulating and antineoplastic activities. Upon isolation, transduction, expansion ex vivo and re-introduction into the patient, the autologous KRAS mutant-specific TCRs gene engineered PBLs target and bind to KRAS mutants-expressing tumor cells, resulting in a cytotoxic T-lymphocyte (CTL)-mediated killing of KRAS mutants-expressing tumor cells. KRAS, a member of the RAS family of oncogenes, serves an important role in cell signaling, division and differentiation. Mutations of KRAS may induce constitutive signal transduction leading to tumor cell proliferation, invasion, and metastasis.

label.value: PEX16 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in peroxisome membrane biogenesis and peroxisome protein recruitment.

label.value: PEX16 wt Allele

value.value: Human PEX16 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 11p11.2 and is approximately 9 kb in length. This allele, which encodes peroxisomal membrane protein PEX16 protein, plays a role in peroxisome biogenesis. Mutation of the gene is associated with peroxisomal biogenesis disorder types 8A and 8B.

label.value: Peroxisomal Membrane Protein PEX16

value.value: Peroxisomal membrane protein PEX16 (336 aa, ~39 kDa) is encoded by the human PEX16 gene. This protein is involved in peroxisome membrane assembly.

label.value: Fibroblast Growth Factor

value.value: A family of structurally-related growth factors with high affinity for heparin. These proteins modulate cell proliferation, angiogenesis, wound healing, embryogenesis and paracrine signaling pathways. Fibroblast growth factors (FGF) stimulate signal transduction through binding to specific members of the fibroblast growth factor receptors (FGFR) family tyrosine kinases.
